items.title: Awesome Cl
items.content_text:
### Lem / Third-party APIs

*   [Lem (‚≠ê2.7k)](https://github.com/lem-project/lem) - a ready to use, Emacs-like, Slime-based
    editor tailored for Common Lisp development out of the box, as well as other programming languages with its built-in LSP client. With ncurses, Electron and SDL2 interfaces. [MIT](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT).
    *   [Lem 2.0 (‚≠ê2.7k)](https://github.com/lem-project/lem/releases/tag/v2.0.0), released on May, 2023, added the SDL2 frontend, thus mouse support, graphic capabilities and Windows support, among other new features.
    *   see also: an [opengl frontend (‚≠ê38)](https://github.com/pupcraft/lem-opengl), [Lem in Docker (‚≠ê5)](https://github.com/40ants/lem-docker), [lem-pareto (‚≠ê38)](https://github.com/40ants/lem-pareto).
items.content_html:
